																	<p style=3D"margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0px;">I singled out =
the SEC commissioner, currently the most powerful figure in college sports,=
 but this honor could have been bestowed on everyone involved with creating=
 the College Football Playoff schedule. About a year ago, as you might reca=
ll, NFL executives tried to convince the CFP <em>not</em> to schedule games=
 on the third Saturday of December=E2=80=94a day on which the NFL has histo=
rically held games. Nevertheless, the CFP grinfuckers went ahead and put <e=
m>three</em> games on that Saturday, including two that ESPN sublicensed to=
 TNT: SMU vs. Penn State at noon and Clemson vs. Texas at 4 p.m.=C2=A0</p>
																	<p style=3D"margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0px;">=C2=A0</p>
																	<p style=3D"margin: 0;">Naturally, the NFL=E2=80=99s own <=
